news.title: Kaisa delays offshore debt revamp talks on uncertain sector outlook: Sources
news.para: The second-largest U.S. dollar bond issuer among Chinese developers after China Evergrande Group, Kaisa has been in the process of restructuring its $12 billion offshore debt after defaulting on some bonds last year.

news.title: Haryana RERA awards 60 days' civil imprisonment to ILD builder
news.para: Adjudicating officer (AO) Rajender Kumar pronounced the sentence in the matter of Garima Gupta vs ILD Millennium Private Limited.

news.title: Ludhiana: Dhandhari construction and demolition waste plant gets March deadline
news.para: The municipal corporation (MC) is yet to complete the construction of the C&D waste plant in Dhandhari for the past many months, and even now the officials claim it will see its completion by March, next year.

news.title: Chandigarh: Migratory bird path blocks IT Park housing project
news.para: The National Board for Wildlife (NBW) in its meeting held on October 13 took the project up for discussion and turned it down. The board is responsible for promotion of conservation and development of wildlife and forests.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh to lease out vacant lands to boost revenue
news.para: The Centre observed that vast extent of lands was left unoccupied giving scope for encroachment. It noted that leasing of such properties will help local bodies to improve its revenues at least by 63 per cent over the present revenues.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body demolishes building connected to RERA scam
news.para: The KDMC on Thursday demolished a ground plus four storey building built by developer Shivsagar Yadav in Dombivli.

news.title: Violations may go up, no mechanism to check all buildings in Gurugram
news.para: Under the new system, the district town planners and assistant town planners of the town and country planning department can conduct random checks on 10% of OCs issued by the architects.

news.title: Chennai: Parandur needs masterplan to become modern aeropolis
news.para: The selling point – own a house or a plot near the greenfield airport -- is a signal that there is bound to be chaotic and unregulated development as firms are pushing up prices and gearing up to buy up land.

news.title: Aurangabad civic body to collect property tax at doorstep
news.para: AMC commissioner Abhijit Chaudhari on Thursday said the tax recovery staff would visit citizens at their properties with the PoS machines seeking payment of property tax through cash, cheque, or virtual modes.

news.title: Local bodies in Uttar Pradesh to have standard building bylaws
news.para: The housing and urban planning department has the mandate of framing the building bylaws and ensuring only planned development takes place within the regulated areas.

news.title: Gujarat: Illegal construction on common plots can't be regularized
news.para: Illegal construction by a member on the common plot of a society will not be regularized under the current Gujarat Regularization of Unauthorized Development Ordinance (GRUDO) 2022, which came into force on October 17.

news.title: Tamil Nadu Housing Board allots 464 plots at four sites in Trichy through lots
news.para: The process was live-streamed to ensure transparency. A total of 894 plots of varying sizes ranging between 345 square feet and 2,400 square feet went for allocation through the TNHB office at KK Nagar.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA prepares list of RWAs & residents who have not paid maintenance charges
news.para: Till October this year, the GDA has listed 114 defaulters who have dues worth around Rs 84 crore. These include RWAs, single-plot owners, educational institutions and commercial establishments, mostly in Indirapuram.

news.title: Karnataka: I-T department detects Rs 1,300 crore black income after raids on builders
news.para: "So far, the search actions have led to the detection of unaccounted income of more than Rs 1,300 crore. "Undisclosed assets in the nature of cash and gold jewellery worth more than Rs 24 crore have also been seized," the Central Board of Direct Taxes said.

news.title: BMC gets nod to not revise capital value of properties in Mumbai
news.para: The cabinet approved an amendment to Section 154(1d) of the BMC Act. Section 154(1d) allows the current value of properties to be revised once every five years.
